space-before-function-paren.option:
This rule has a string option or an object option:

{
    "space-before-function-paren": ["error", "always"],
    // or
    "space-before-function-paren": ["error", {
        "anonymous": "always",
        "named": "always",
        "asyncArrow": "always"
    }],
}

- always(default) requires a space followed by the(of arguments.
- neverdisallows any space followed by the(of arguments.

The string option does not check async arrow function expressions for backward compatibility.

You can also use a separate option for each type of function.
Each of the following options can be set to"always","never", or"ignore". The default is"always".

- anonymousis for anonymous function expressions (e.g.function () {}).
- namedis for named function expressions (e.g.function foo () {}).
- asyncArrowis for async arrow function expressions (e.g.async () => {}).

“always”

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with the default"always"option:

/*eslint space-before-function-paren: "error"*/

function foo() {
    // ...
}

var bar = function() {
    // ...
};

var bar = function foo() {
    // ...
};

class Foo {
    constructor() {
        // ...
    }
}

var baz = {
    bar() {
        // ...
    }
};

var baz = async() => 1

